<subSubSection id="9BBD65058074E13FFF39FF210052B97B" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D318368E8074E13FFF39FF210052B97B" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="E1D3EA9C8074E13FFF39FF210028B8D7" bold="true" box="[199,308,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="14A74D0D8074E13FFEBAFF21033AB8D6" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1906" box="[324,550,152,179]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scinidae" genus="Scina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarginata">
<emphasis id="E1D3EA9C8074E13FFEBAFF21033AB8D6" box="[324,550,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Scina submarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur at depths between 200 and 
<quantity id="145F9B6B8074E13FFBC0FF21058BB8D7" box="[1086,1175,153,179]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" unit="m" value="4000.0">4000 m</quantity>
. It is relatively easy to distinguish by features such as the distal extension of propodus in pereopod 1, but not in pereopod 2 (like in 
<taxonomicName id="14A74D0D8074E13FFAB5FF0501C3B89E" baseAuthorityName="Bovallius" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Malacostraca" family="Scinidae" genus="Scina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="E1D3EA9C8074E13FFAB5FF0501C3B89E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">S. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the basis of pereopod 5 with long anterodistal projection. The sizes of the two examined females were 4.5 and 5.8 mm.
</paragraph>
